Some people like to tell everyone around themselves how busy they are so that nobody asks them to take on another task. Also, some people like to seem very busy because only then they can feel important. If you also feel very busy or tell everyone around that you are too busy, you probably are not managing your time well.

The Laws of Attraction are strict. You cannot send out waves of negative energy, and expect to attract only the positive treatment in return. Your treatment from others comes directly from your treatment of yourself. For example, if you are constantly criticizing yourself, it is very likely that you will magnetize an opportunity where others will criticize you also. Is that what you really want in your life? 
The biggest source of "stuff" that we send out can be found in our thoughts and beliefs. This is actually very liberating because, while we may not be able to do much about our looks, we always have the option to change the way we think. Pr-aa (Pharoah) meaning, literally, "Great House" originally referred to the king's royal palace. However, during the reign of Thutmose III (circa 1479-1425 BC), after the foreign rule of the Hyksos, the term pr-aa ( a compound word derived from two hieroglyphs -- pr "house" and aa "column") was only used in larger phrases such as smr pr-aa 'Courtier of the High House' with specific reference to the buildings of the court or palace. From the 12th dynasty onward the word appears in a wish "formula": 'Great House, may it live, prosper and be in health'. The earliest instance of pr-aa specifically being used to address the ruler is in a letter Amenhotep IV (Akhenaten [1353-1336 BC]), which is addressed to 'Pharoah, all life, prosperity, and health!.' During the 18th dynasty the title Pharoah was employed as a reverential designation of the ruler.  #DataDayDxpe Praadigi #BTS #digitale
